KW  - Endogenous growth
KW  - Cross-sectional data
KW  - Human capital
KW  - Openness
AB  - We estimate two versions of Romer’s model of endogenous technological change that allow for population growth and human capital accumulation. In one of these versions, estimates from international cross-sectional data yield parameter values that are consistent with prior information, and tests of overidentifying restrictions are not rejected. Trade openness increases the effectiveness with which human capital generates new knowledge, and improves the model’s predictive performance. The Romer model represents a valuable template on which to build more sophisticated models of endogenous long-run growth without scale effects.
ER  - 

