AB  - This note generalizes to second generation models of currency crises the arbitrage-based approach first applied by Flood and Garber to first generation models. Deriving policy-switching rules based on the ‘shadow exchange rate’ facilitates the comparative analysis of the literature. Using the ‘shadow rate’, we provide and discuss an example of a common mechanism generating multiple equilibria in both first and second generation models.
